[('50. Playboi Carti- Sky', [['‚ÄúSky‚Äù is an ode to getting high and what life feels like under the influence of weed, lean, and other drugs. The chorus suggests Carti indulges in various substances to reach a state of numbness. He also addresses his feelings towards his girl, and how he has fallen out of love for her over time.

The instrumental features video game-esque synths, booming 808s, and is done by Art Dealer who he previously collaborated with on ‚ÄúLong Time (Intro)‚Äù on Die Lit.']]), ('47. Saweetie- Best Friend (feat. Doja Cat)', [['‚ÄúBest Friend,‚Äù the first collaboration between Saweetie and Doja Cat, was prematurely released by her own label on Apple Music and Deezer on 4 December 2020, a month before the scheduled release. The song serves as the third single for Saweetie‚Äôs upcoming debut album, Pretty Bitch Music.

Shortly after it hit streaming services, the rapper called out Warner Records to express the frustration and disappointment she experienced over the accident.


I feel disrespected. I‚Äôm hands on with ALL of my creative & had such a dope rollout for ‚Äòbest friends‚Äô.

We put so much work into the visual & we shot for days for this super cinematic girl anthem. And for this to happen? wow‚Ä¶.']]), ('49. Lil Mosey- Holy Water', [['In ‚ÄúHoly Water,‚Äù Lil Mosey details his contradiction between drinking holy water, water blessed by a religious figure, and living a trap lifestyle complete with theft and sexual relationships.

Mosey originally announced the track‚Äôs release for January 12, 2021 in a TikTok caption, however hours later, he revealed that it had been delayed in a Twitter reply. In an Instagram post on January 21, Mosey announced the track‚Äôs release date for the 25th, his nineteenth birthday.

The track will likely serve as the second single to Mosey‚Äôs upcoming mixtape, Universal.']]), ('48. Megan Thee Stallion- Body', [['On ‚ÄúBody,‚Äù Megan Thee Stallion brags about her desirability, being the envy of other women, and the fantasy of their men.  It served as the fourth single to Good News, and dropped the night of the album‚Äôs release with a video. The track features a rapid-paced instrumental built around a sample of a woman moaning.

The music video that dropped with it featured cameos including Blac Chyna,  Taraji P. Henson, Jordyn Woods, Asian Da Brat, among others.']]), ('45. Megan Thee Stallion- Cry Baby (feat. DaBaby)', [['On ‚ÄúCry Baby,‚Äù Megan Thee Stallion recruits frequent collaborator DaBaby for another quality banger. On the track, Meg and DaBaby talk about their active sex lives, claiming that both of their body counts are so sky-high that even their friends and parents are being a ‚Äúcry baby‚Äù about it. The track‚Äôs ominous instrumental is built around a crying sample and features a heavy-hitting beat.']]), ('44. SpotemGottem- Beat Box', [['this song gose hard']]), ('40. NLE Choppa- Moonlight (feat. Big Sean)', [['NLE Choppa enlists Detroit rapper Big Sean for the first time to rap about problems with killings and their past bad habits changing to good habits in life on ‚ÄúMoonlight.‚Äù

This song is produced by TnTXD, Tahj Money, YoungTN, and Rara, who all wrote it along with the two artists. The middle two producers return for beats throughout most of the project.

The official music video for this song was released on January 8, 2021. Unsurprisingly, the two sit in the moonlight, performing their respective selections of it. It predominantly focuses on their come up and switching from negative values to positive values.']]), ('39. Ty Dolla $ign- Spicy (feat. Post Malone)', [['‚ÄúSpicy‚Äù is the fourth single from Ty Dolla $ign‚Äôs third studio album Featuring Ty Dolla $ign. The Los Angeles artist is joined by rapper and singer Post Malone for a melodic collaboration that follows their 2018 hit ‚ÄúPsycho‚Äù‚Äîwhich Post nods to in his verse.

The theme of the song focuses on the duo‚Äôs wild lifestyle, filled with the company of beautiful women interested in their money.

The official music video for ‚ÄúSpicy‚Äù was released on November 25, 2020, one month after the song‚Äôs release.']]), ('37. Lil Durk- Finesse Out The Gang Way (feat. Lil Baby)', [['Lil Durk reunites with Lil Baby on ‚ÄúFinesse Out the Gang Way.‚Äù The two rap on the Chopsquad DJ-produced instrumental about the struggles that they faced before starting their music careers, whilst dropping references to expensive items that they now own.

The official lyric video for the song premiered alongside its release as part of the release of the deluxe version of The Voice on January 29, 2021.']]), ('42. Kid Cudi- Tequila Shots', [['Kid Cudi embarks on the final chapter of the Man on the Moon trilogy by reflecting on past struggles and ongoing internal wars.

Cudi depicts imagery of a storm stirring up within him, but he can‚Äôt back down from the fight, despite his fears of crashing. He also mimics Common‚Äôs narration as a callback to the first Man on the Moon.

In an interview with Zane Lowe, Cudi expressed that ‚ÄúTequila Shots‚Äù was one of the first tracks he finished for Man on the Moon III‚Äîeven before he knew he was going to make the album. While discussing the song, he shared:

It sounds like such an introduction, it sounds like you pick right back up where we left off ten years ago.

The production features a high-pitched synth over a pressing bass with a melodic hook reminiscent of his 2009 self, courtesy of friend and producer, Dot Da Genius, and production duo, Take a Daytrip.

In the Making of Man on the Moon III livestream on December 12th, 2020,  Dot Da Genius and Daytrip explained that the song was created in the first time they met Cudi after the release of THE SCOTTS. The song acquired its name ‚ÄúTequila Shots‚Äù because they took tequila shots to celebrate the song‚Äôs release.']])]
